message.content: In 1996, a new variant of the M2 protein was discovered in influenza B viruses. This variant, designated as the BM2 protein, is encoded by a separate open reading frame within the same RNA segment as the original M2 protein. The BM2 protein plays a role in the virus's ability to replicate and infect host cells, and its discovery has provided new insights into the structure and function of influenza B viruses.
